Neymar’s move to Barcelona is on the brink of collapse, after Ousmane Dembele’s agent said his player wouldn’t be leaving the Nou Camp. Paris Saint-Germain asked for Dembele included in a deal that would see Neymar return to the Spanish champions. But the winger’s agent, Moussa Sissoko, has told Telefoot that the 22-year-old won’t be going anywhere. “He is staying 100 per cent. “There is no chance he will leave. He wants and will win at Barca,” Sissoko said. Dembele has endured an injury-ravaged spell at Barcelona, since signing from Borussia Dortmund in 2017. While he scored 14 times for Barcelona last season, he only managed to make 20 starts in LaLiga. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.